Java Heap is used throughout the app, but Stack is only used for the method or methods currently running
The Heap Space contains all objects are created , but Stack contains any reference to the those objects.
Objects stored in the Heap can be accessed throughout the application. Primitive local variables are only
accessed the Stack Memory blocks that contains their methods.
Memory allocation in the Heap Space us accessed through a complex, young generation, old- generation system.
Stack is accessed a last in, first-out (LIFO) memory allocation system.
Heap space exists as ling as the application runs and is larger than Stack, which is temporary,but faster.
